WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.717 --> 00:00:04.216
What's your sin?

2
00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:08.220
I was a horrible mother.

3
00:00:08.222 --> 00:00:11.057
You are shamelessly
sucking up so that I'll free you

4
00:00:11.059 --> 00:00:13.993
so you can run amok and gum up
my operation once again.

5
00:00:13.995 --> 00:00:16.629
Who is there left
for you to trust?

6
00:00:17.632 --> 00:00:19.498
You and I
are very much alike.

7
00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:21.233
Yeah. except I didn't kill
my brother.

8
00:00:21.235 --> 00:00:23.669
The Mark can be transferred
to someone who's worthy.

9
00:00:23.671 --> 00:00:24.837
But make me a promise
first.

10
00:00:24.839 --> 00:00:26.939
When I call you.
use the Blade on me.

11
00:00:26.941 --> 00:00:28.341
Don't you think that if Cain
knew how to remove the Mark.

12
00:00:28.343 --> 00:00:31.177
he would have done it.
like. centuries ago?

13
00:00:31.179 --> 00:00:32.678
I'm done
trying to find a cure. Sammy.

14
00:00:32.680 --> 00:00:34.080
Dean. Cass is so close.

15
00:00:34.082 --> 00:00:36.115
Maybe Cass is
onto something with Cain --

16
00:00:36.117 --> 00:00:37.683
but the answer
is not out there.

17
00:00:37.685 --> 00:00:38.918
It's with me.

18
00:00:38.920 --> 00:00:40.119
So. I'm gonna fight it

19
00:00:40.121 --> 00:00:42.221
till I can't fight it
anymore.

20
00:01:00.775 --> 00:01:02.708
Lights out in five.

21
00:01:04.145 --> 00:01:06.512
Hey. any mail?

22
00:01:06.514 --> 00:01:07.880
Oh. the usual --

23
00:01:07.882 --> 00:01:10.716
postcards
from anti-penalty folk.

24
00:01:10.718 --> 00:01:13.486
proposals
from your lady admirers.

25
00:01:13.488 --> 00:01:15.254
You said
you were done with those.

26
00:01:17.959 --> 00:01:23.663
Hey. how's your wife.
by the way -- Amanda?

27
00:01:23.665 --> 00:01:25.464
That's her name.
isn't it?

28
00:01:29.337 --> 00:01:32.672
You know I killed
an Amanda once?

29
00:01:33.741 --> 00:01:37.276
My fourth.

30
00:01:40.682 --> 00:01:44.150
I'd do your wife the same.
buddy.

31
00:01:44.152 --> 00:01:47.119
only slower.

32
00:01:47.121 --> 00:01:50.623
Two weeks from Tuesday.
Tommy.

33
00:01:50.625 --> 00:01:52.491
Yeah.

34
00:01:52.493 --> 00:01:54.493
Let's do it!

35
00:01:54.495 --> 00:01:57.430
Let's do it now.
tonight!

36
00:02:29.097 --> 00:02:30.796
Tolliver giving you
the usual grief?

37
00:02:31.999 --> 00:02:33.566
Nothing new.

38
00:02:49.817 --> 00:02:52.852
I can't wait
till he's gone.

39
00:03:14.542 --> 00:03:16.442
Who the hell are you?

40
00:03:16.444 --> 00:03:17.943
How'd you get in here?!

41
00:03:17.945 --> 00:03:21.113
I've gone by many names
in this life.

42
00:03:21.115 --> 00:03:23.415
The father of murder
is one of them.

43
00:03:25.953 --> 00:03:28.821
And by the state's count.

44
00:03:28.823 --> 00:03:31.557
you've taken six lives yourself.
Tommy.

45
00:03:31.559 --> 00:03:36.362
Although by<i> my</i> count.
it's nine.

46
00:03:36.364 --> 00:03:39.098
Oh. come on.

47
00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:40.499
You aren't one of those

48
00:03:40.501 --> 00:03:42.968
“it wasn't me” type fellas.
are you?

49
00:03:42.970 --> 00:03:46.906
Because I know
you're a killer.

50
00:03:46.908 --> 00:03:48.908
just like me.

51
00:03:50.578 --> 00:03:53.779
Yeah. I did it.

52
00:03:53.781 --> 00:03:55.748
Honesty.

53
00:03:55.750 --> 00:03:57.349
That's good.

54
00:03:59.287 --> 00:04:01.287
That's the spirit!

55
00:04:01.289 --> 00:04:03.189
Ugh!

56
00:04:06.994 --> 00:04:11.163
Now. I bet you're wondering
what I'm doing here.

57
00:04:11.165 --> 00:04:14.466
Did I come to punish you
or save you?

58
00:04:14.468 --> 00:04:17.903
Well...

59
00:04:17.905 --> 00:04:20.840
The truth is. Tommy...

60
00:04:20.842 --> 00:04:23.075
I'm here to do both.

61
00:04:28.436 --> 00:04:32.436
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Supernatural 10x14 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Executioner's Song</font>
Original Air Date on February 17. 2015

62
00:04:32.460 --> 00:04:38.960
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

63
00:04:40.587 --> 00:04:43.688
- The Zodiac?
- Seven victims.

64
00:04:43.690 --> 00:04:45.756
Dahmer?
17.

65
00:04:45.758 --> 00:04:48.759
That's some freaky stuff. man.
It's a whole new side of you.

66
00:04:48.761 --> 00:04:51.329
It's called true crime. Dean.
It's a hobby.

67
00:04:51.331 --> 00:04:54.265
No. Bass fishing. needlepoint --
that's a hobby. okay?

68
00:04:54.267 --> 00:04:56.200
Collecting
serial-killer stats --

69
00:04:56.202 --> 00:04:58.102
that's --
that is an illness.

70
00:04:59.405 --> 00:05:01.672
Get your badge.
Yeah.

71
00:05:08.515 --> 00:05:10.081
<i> Hello. gentlemen.</i>
<i>State the nature of your visit.</i>

72
00:05:10.083 --> 00:05:12.917
From the office
of the Inspector General.

73
00:05:12.919 --> 00:05:15.153
Got an appointment
with the warden.

74
00:05:15.155 --> 00:05:16.921
<i>Thank you.</i>
<i>Parking is to the left.</i>

75
00:05:16.923 --> 00:05:20.391
<i>Look for</i>
<i>visitor parking only.</i>

76
00:05:20.393 --> 00:05:22.527
All right.
so what are the stats

77
00:05:22.529 --> 00:05:24.462
on this. uh.
vanishing act here?

78
00:05:24.464 --> 00:05:28.099
Tommy Tolliver was convicted
of six murders back in '09.

79
00:05:28.101 --> 00:05:29.934
but those are
just the ones that stuck.

80
00:05:29.936 --> 00:05:31.302
According to the news.

81
00:05:31.304 --> 00:05:34.071
he escaped from a locked cell
on death row.

82
00:05:34.073 --> 00:05:37.241
this inexplicable.
Houdini-esque escape.

83
00:05:37.243 --> 00:05:38.743
So what are we thinking?

84
00:05:38.745 --> 00:05:41.279
Some sort of
a mass-murdering magician?

85
00:05:41.281 --> 00:05:43.214
Yeah.
or a teleporting demon

86
00:05:43.216 --> 00:05:45.716
or a who knows what that
can walk through Supermax walls.

87
00:05:45.718 --> 00:05:47.618
Could be in our wheelhouse.

88
00:05:47.620 --> 00:05:49.720
Yeah.<i> your</i> wheelhouse.

89
00:05:49.722 --> 00:05:52.290
“Hobby.”

90
00:05:58.198 --> 00:06:00.131
Warden Skeiff?

91
00:06:00.133 --> 00:06:01.899
Uh. Inspectors Moore
and Ranaldo.

92
00:06:01.901 --> 00:06:03.167
We spoke on the phone.

93
00:06:03.169 --> 00:06:05.536
Yeah.
Welcome to death row.

94
00:06:05.538 --> 00:06:07.271
Have a look.

95
00:06:07.273 --> 00:06:12.877
But good luck finding anything
out of TDJC compliance.

96
00:06:17.517 --> 00:06:20.117
So. why don't you tell me
what happened?

97
00:06:20.119 --> 00:06:22.153
The night
Tolliver disappeared.

98
00:06:22.155 --> 00:06:24.755
our little ship was running
as tight as ever.

99
00:06:24.757 --> 00:06:26.691
and I got documentation
to prove it.

100
00:06:26.693 --> 00:06:28.859
Do you stand by
what the press is saying --

101
00:06:28.861 --> 00:06:30.861
locked cell.
no security breach.

102
00:06:30.863 --> 00:06:32.096
no guard misconduct?

103
00:06:32.098 --> 00:06:33.698
Which press?

104
00:06:33.700 --> 00:06:35.833
Mainstream media
is calling for my head.

105
00:06:35.835 --> 00:06:37.368
said I was
grossly incompetent.

106
00:06:37.370 --> 00:06:38.703
But the tabloids.
they're saying --

107
00:06:38.705 --> 00:06:40.338
They're saying
it's magic

108
00:06:40.340 --> 00:06:44.075
That Tommy pulled off
some dark miracle to escape.

109
00:06:45.278 --> 00:06:46.577
You saying
you believe that?

110
00:06:46.579 --> 00:06:48.446
I'm saying there was
some kind of magician

111
00:06:48.448 --> 00:06:50.781
on the block last night.
but it wasn't Tommy.

112
00:06:53.686 --> 00:06:57.088
That's right before
Tolliver vanished.

113
00:06:59.425 --> 00:07:01.759
Was that a brownout?

114
00:07:01.761 --> 00:07:03.928
That was my thought.
but then...

115
00:07:06.699 --> 00:07:08.165
Is it one of the guards?

116
00:07:08.167 --> 00:07:09.567
Nope.

117
00:07:09.569 --> 00:07:12.737
But I don't know who he is.
how he got in.

118
00:07:12.739 --> 00:07:15.106
or how he and Tolliver
got out.

119
00:07:15.108 --> 00:07:16.841
Can you zoom in on that?

120
00:07:16.843 --> 00:07:18.075
Can and have.

121
00:07:18.077 --> 00:07:20.077
Too dark to make out
much of anything.

122
00:07:20.079 --> 00:07:21.946
Do it.

123
00:07:24.217 --> 00:07:25.816
Freeze it.

124
00:07:26.986 --> 00:07:28.819
Blow it up.

125
00:07:44.771 --> 00:07:47.338
Gonna answer that?

126
00:07:47.340 --> 00:07:49.006
Not at this moment.

127
00:07:50.576 --> 00:07:53.411
You're wasting your time.

128
00:07:53.413 --> 00:07:56.080
I told you.
I don't know where he is.

129
00:07:56.082 --> 00:07:59.650
Me and Cain ain't friends.

130
00:07:59.652 --> 00:08:01.018
He kills demons.

131
00:08:01.020 --> 00:08:03.354
Low-level guys like me
keep our distance.

132
00:08:04.590 --> 00:08:06.924
You sure about that?

133
00:08:06.926 --> 00:08:08.859
All right!

134
00:08:08.861 --> 00:08:10.261
All right.

135
00:08:14.801 --> 00:08:17.935
He's been seen.
past few months.

136
00:08:17.937 --> 00:08:20.438
making passes
through Bogg's marsh.

137
00:08:20.440 --> 00:08:23.374
one county over.

138
00:08:23.376 --> 00:08:25.910
No one knows why.
what for.

139
00:08:25.912 --> 00:08:28.979
Like I said.
we keep our distance.

140
00:08:32.652 --> 00:08:34.285
And that's all you know.

141
00:08:34.287 --> 00:08:37.088
Yes.

142
00:08:37.090 --> 00:08:39.690
Yes. I swear.

143
00:08:44.063 --> 00:08:46.997
Okay.

144
00:08:49.035 --> 00:08:53.137
Aaaaah!

145
00:08:53.139 --> 00:08:57.975
86 last quarter.
while I only get credit for 48.

146
00:08:57.977 --> 00:08:59.710
A-and I was working
with Alban

147
00:08:59.712 --> 00:09:01.545
on nearly all
of those soul jobs.

148
00:09:03.182 --> 00:09:06.050
If you don't arrive at a point
within the next 10 seconds.

149
00:09:06.052 --> 00:09:07.284
so help me. I'll --

150
00:09:07.286 --> 00:09:08.652
As a crossroads demon.

151
00:09:08.654 --> 00:09:10.554
I have received less credit
than I am due

152
00:09:10.556 --> 00:09:12.056
for soul collections...

153
00:09:13.593 --> 00:09:15.226
...my king.

154
00:09:18.464 --> 00:09:21.599
So you're looking
for a promotion?

155
00:09:21.601 --> 00:09:23.934
No. I'm just asking...

156
00:09:25.371 --> 00:09:28.406
I'm merely suggesting
that I get credit

157
00:09:28.408 --> 00:09:30.074
for the work that I did
beside Alban.

158
00:09:30.076 --> 00:09:32.777
Equal credit
for equal work.

159
00:09:32.779 --> 00:09:34.879
Fine.
You can have your credit.

160
00:09:34.881 --> 00:09:37.948
Thank you.
The wee man! Ugh!

161
00:09:39.218 --> 00:09:42.987
Mother.
you have. uh. an opinion

162
00:09:42.989 --> 00:09:44.922
you'd like to share
with the room?

163
00:09:44.924 --> 00:09:46.223
Oh. no.

164
00:09:46.225 --> 00:09:48.159
Private thought.

165
00:09:48.161 --> 00:09:51.562
nothing to do with you
or the affairs of the court.

166
00:09:55.535 --> 00:09:57.902
It's just
not what I would do.

167
00:09:57.904 --> 00:10:02.840
Oh. enlighten us all.
What would you do?

168
00:10:02.842 --> 00:10:07.411
This demon asks you
to equalize credit

169
00:10:07.413 --> 00:10:09.013
for his and another's work --

170
00:10:09.015 --> 00:10:11.982
split the baby.
if you will.

171
00:10:11.984 --> 00:10:18.889
Well  then I would
well and truly split the baby.

172
00:10:20.693 --> 00:10:27.665
I'd cut this puling. pathetic.
greed-grubbing git in two.

173
00:10:27.667 --> 00:10:28.966
literally.

174
00:10:28.968 --> 00:10:30.868
then I'd nail
his bloody halves

175
00:10:30.870 --> 00:10:32.369
to the doors of the court --

176
00:10:32.371 --> 00:10:37.007
a reminder to all
not to waste the king's time.

177
00:10:37.009 --> 00:10:39.877
Whiners beget whiners.

178
00:10:39.879 --> 00:10:42.279
You can't reward
behavior like that --

179
00:10:42.281 --> 00:10:45.516
why I never gave in when you
asked for sweeties as a child.

180
00:10:45.518 --> 00:10:48.285
no matter how much you cried.

181
00:10:48.915 --> 00:10:52.033
Well. you were a very...

182
00:10:53.857 --> 00:10:56.328
chunky child. darling.

183
00:10:56.329 --> 00:10:57.695
Bit of a bloater.

184
00:10:57.697 --> 00:10:59.263
That's enough.

185
00:11:07.106 --> 00:11:09.773
What'll it be. sir?

186
00:11:16.549 --> 00:11:20.017
Let's do...

187
00:11:20.019 --> 00:11:21.552
What she said.

188
00:11:21.554 --> 00:11:23.420
Wha...

189
00:11:23.422 --> 00:11:25.022
N-no. no. no!

190
00:11:25.024 --> 00:11:27.224
No. no. no. no!

191
00:11:27.226 --> 00:11:28.659
Come on!

192
00:11:29.996 --> 00:11:31.662
That's my boy.

193
00:11:37.169 --> 00:11:38.536
So?

194
00:11:38.538 --> 00:11:40.304
Cass is still not answering.

195
00:11:40.306 --> 00:11:42.840
Great. Well. I have been looking
into Tommy Tolliver.

196
00:11:42.842 --> 00:11:44.208
seeing if I can figure out

197
00:11:44.210 --> 00:11:46.176
why Cain went to the trouble
of springing him.

198
00:11:46.178 --> 00:11:47.545
And?

199
00:11:47.547 --> 00:11:48.746
Still pretty unclear.

200
00:11:48.748 --> 00:11:51.081
I did find this blotter
out of Orlando

201
00:11:51.083 --> 00:11:52.750
about his dad.
Leon Tolliver.

202
00:11:52.752 --> 00:11:54.251
Uh. like father. like son.

203
00:11:54.253 --> 00:11:57.454
Convicted felon. fresh warrant
for an assault charge.

204
00:11:57.456 --> 00:12:00.424
but he's gone missing.
hasn't been seen in a week.

205
00:12:00.426 --> 00:12:02.326
You think
the two are connected?

206
00:12:02.328 --> 00:12:05.529
I mean. the police just assumed
he fled the warrant.

207
00:12:05.531 --> 00:12:09.033
but if Cain took Tommy.
it might not be a coincidence.

208
00:12:09.035 --> 00:12:12.503
So. what. Cain's got a vendetta
against the entire family?

209
00:12:12.505 --> 00:12:14.371
Maybe.

210
00:12:18.210 --> 00:12:19.443
It's Cass.

211
00:12:20.980 --> 00:12:22.279
Hey. where you at?

212
00:12:22.281 --> 00:12:23.547
Illinois.

213
00:12:23.549 --> 00:12:25.049
Hey. Cass. we got a lead.

214
00:12:25.051 --> 00:12:27.618
Cain abducted
a Texas death row inmate

215
00:12:27.620 --> 00:12:29.219
named Tommy Tolliver.

216
00:12:31.157 --> 00:12:33.190
He's dead.
What?

217
00:12:33.192 --> 00:12:34.758
How do you know?

218
00:12:34.760 --> 00:12:36.327
Call it an educated guess.

219
00:12:36.329 --> 00:12:39.330
Cain has been very busy.

220
00:12:42.802 --> 00:12:45.369
Okay. where are you?
We'll come to you.

221
00:12:48.074 --> 00:12:50.140
I'll call you back.

222
00:13:01.454 --> 00:13:04.254
Hello. Castiel.

223
00:13:11.241 --> 00:13:13.008
What have you done?

224
00:13:13.010 --> 00:13:15.144
These bodies?

225
00:13:15.146 --> 00:13:19.081
Just cleaning up a mess I made
a long time ago.

226
00:13:19.083 --> 00:13:21.717
Cain.
I know what you were.

227
00:13:21.719 --> 00:13:24.720
But you'd resisted
for so long.

228
00:13:24.722 --> 00:13:26.255
What can I say?

229
00:13:26.257 --> 00:13:28.324
I got the taste back.

230
00:13:29.494 --> 00:13:31.660
With Abaddon's army
gunning for me.

231
00:13:31.662 --> 00:13:34.396
I had to
take up arms again.

232
00:13:34.398 --> 00:13:36.298
and I liked how it felt.

233
00:13:36.300 --> 00:13:38.634
Those were demons.

234
00:13:38.636 --> 00:13:39.969
These...

235
00:13:39.971 --> 00:13:42.605
Humans.

236
00:13:42.607 --> 00:13:46.675
Eh. the Mark thirsts
for all kinds.

237
00:13:46.677 --> 00:13:48.711
This is a massacre.

238
00:13:50.515 --> 00:13:52.848
Yes.

239
00:13:52.850 --> 00:13:55.117
And soon
it'll be a genocide.

240
00:13:57.822 --> 00:14:02.525
My children.
my whole poisoned issue.

241
00:14:04.128 --> 00:14:05.794
A lot of them out there
right now --

242
00:14:05.796 --> 00:14:09.465
killers.
fighters. thieves.

243
00:14:09.467 --> 00:14:11.967
some more peaceful
than others.

244
00:14:11.969 --> 00:14:16.539
But they still carry it --
the disease.

245
00:14:16.541 --> 00:14:19.175
If the Mark wants blood.
I'll give it mine.

246
00:14:19.177 --> 00:14:21.143
You'll kill them all?

247
00:14:21.145 --> 00:14:24.446
You are Adam and Eve's
firstborn.

248
00:14:24.448 --> 00:14:27.016
Your descendents
are Legion.

249
00:14:27.018 --> 00:14:31.120
At most.
I'm culling...1 in 10.

250
00:14:31.122 --> 00:14:32.388
Of everyone.

251
00:14:32.390 --> 00:14:33.756
I've got time.

252
00:14:35.059 --> 00:14:37.726
How's Dean. by the way?

253
00:14:37.728 --> 00:14:41.897
I hear he did good.
took Abaddon down.

254
00:14:44.101 --> 00:14:45.901
He's not well.

255
00:14:47.705 --> 00:14:50.839
Even with
the First Blade hidden.

256
00:14:50.841 --> 00:14:53.976
Dean is losing his fight
against the Mark.

257
00:14:53.978 --> 00:14:55.878
If we don't find a cure --

258
00:14:55.880 --> 00:14:57.446
There is no cure.

259
00:14:57.448 --> 00:14:59.582
I'm living proof of that.

260
00:14:59.584 --> 00:15:02.151
But don't worry about Dean.

261
00:15:02.153 --> 00:15:05.487
I'll get to him.
in due time.

262
00:15:09.994 --> 00:15:12.328
Sorry. Castiel.

263
00:15:12.330 --> 00:15:14.496
You're not on my list.

264
00:15:21.239 --> 00:15:24.240
Crowley...

265
00:15:24.242 --> 00:15:27.009
Long day.
I'm sure you must be tired.

266
00:15:27.011 --> 00:15:28.577
But I've had a wee idea.

267
00:15:28.579 --> 00:15:29.812
Yes?

268
00:15:29.814 --> 00:15:32.248
The name Olivette
means little to you.

269
00:15:32.250 --> 00:15:34.783
A high-ranking member
of the grand coven.

270
00:15:34.785 --> 00:15:36.919
the one who led the charge
against me.

271
00:15:36.921 --> 00:15:40.422
Really. it's a grudge.
I won't even deny it.

272
00:15:40.424 --> 00:15:43.425
But she's just come back
to the states.

273
00:15:43.427 --> 00:15:48.230
and I thought if you.
in your kingly beneficence.

274
00:15:48.232 --> 00:15:51.700
would be so kind
as to assist me.

275
00:15:51.702 --> 00:15:55.337
now would be an excellent time
to strike.

276
00:15:58.009 --> 00:16:00.442
Well done. Mother.

277
00:16:00.444 --> 00:16:03.212
Next time
you run a long con.

278
00:16:03.214 --> 00:16:06.682
let more than a few hours
of suspicious.

279
00:16:06.684 --> 00:16:10.386
entirely uncharacteristic
usefulness pass

280
00:16:10.388 --> 00:16:12.221
before making your ask.

281
00:16:12.223 --> 00:16:14.923
You think I had
an ulterior motive.

282
00:16:14.925 --> 00:16:17.393
that I've been
manipulating you?

283
00:16:17.395 --> 00:16:20.029
You couldn't be
more transparent.

284
00:16:20.031 --> 00:16:22.464
Well. duh!

285
00:16:22.466 --> 00:16:25.434
Of course
I was manipulating you!

286
00:16:25.436 --> 00:16:28.270
I am<i> your</i> mother.
after all.

287
00:16:28.272 --> 00:16:32.141
Manipulation's
who we are.

288
00:16:32.143 --> 00:16:34.310
Oh.

289
00:16:34.312 --> 00:16:36.345
My wee sausage.

290
00:16:36.347 --> 00:16:39.515
what matter is it
that I had a motive?

291
00:16:39.517 --> 00:16:41.984
We had fun today.
didn't we?

292
00:16:41.986 --> 00:16:44.186
It was fine.

293
00:16:44.188 --> 00:16:46.388
We could have more.

294
00:16:46.390 --> 00:16:48.023
Get out of this dump.

295
00:16:48.025 --> 00:16:51.427
a break from
these foul-smelling suck-ups.

296
00:16:51.429 --> 00:16:54.029
flex our muscles
in the real world

297
00:16:54.031 --> 00:16:57.700
and in the process take out
a miserable. old witch

298
00:16:57.702 --> 00:17:01.403
who's been standing in my way
for centuries.

299
00:17:02.573 --> 00:17:04.406
What do you say?

300
00:17:14.618 --> 00:17:17.553
I'm sorry I couldn't bring
better news. Dean.

301
00:17:17.555 --> 00:17:18.787
It's not your fault.
Cass.

302
00:17:18.789 --> 00:17:20.255
Thank you.

303
00:17:20.257 --> 00:17:22.191
All right. the sheriff gave me
a few more names.

304
00:17:22.193 --> 00:17:23.525
some preliminary I.D.s
on the bodies.

305
00:17:23.527 --> 00:17:26.128
And?
And it seems to fit Cass' story.

306
00:17:26.130 --> 00:17:29.064
I mean. there's no way to tell
the relation to Cain. obviously.

307
00:17:29.066 --> 00:17:31.667
but he's wiping out entire
families. one after another.

308
00:17:31.669 --> 00:17:34.403
So who's next?
Is he done with the Tollivers?

309
00:17:34.405 --> 00:17:36.338
Uh. I think so.

310
00:17:36.340 --> 00:17:38.507
I mean. Leon didn't have any siblings
or any other children I can see.

311
00:17:38.509 --> 00:17:40.976
and Tommy was never married.
so I...

312
00:17:40.978 --> 00:17:43.612
Oh. come on.
Damn it.

313
00:17:43.614 --> 00:17:45.447
What?

314
00:17:45.449 --> 00:17:48.183
Tommy<i> did</i> have a son.
estranged.

315
00:17:48.185 --> 00:17:50.552
who lives with his mother
in Ohio.

316
00:17:50.554 --> 00:17:53.222
uh. Austin Reynolds.
12 years old.

317
00:17:53.224 --> 00:17:55.290
Is the kid still alive?

318
00:17:57.261 --> 00:17:59.361
As of an hour ago. yeah.

319
00:17:59.363 --> 00:18:01.263
He updated his status.

320
00:18:03.467 --> 00:18:05.067
But. I mean. come on.
It's a kid.

321
00:18:05.069 --> 00:18:06.735
You don't really think
Cain would --

322
00:18:06.737 --> 00:18:08.470
Yes. he would.

323
00:18:08.472 --> 00:18:11.073
There were old men
in those graves. Sam. women.

324
00:18:11.075 --> 00:18:12.341
I mean. you heard Cass.

325
00:18:12.343 --> 00:18:16.145
It's a fire sale.
Everyone must go.

326
00:18:16.147 --> 00:18:19.081
Where you going?

327
00:18:19.083 --> 00:18:21.483
We know
where Cain's gonna be.

328
00:18:23.187 --> 00:18:25.854
The kid's in danger.

329
00:18:25.856 --> 00:18:31.293
Okay. so what. we track him down
to Ohio. and then what?

330
00:18:33.764 --> 00:18:36.298
Then I'll do
what I have to do.

331
00:18:39.336 --> 00:18:41.870
I'll kill Cain.

332
00:18:55.263 --> 00:18:57.230
When he gave me the Mark.

333
00:18:57.232 --> 00:19:00.299
Cain said
that this day would come.

334
00:19:00.301 --> 00:19:01.567
that after I killed Abaddon.

335
00:19:01.569 --> 00:19:03.703
I would have to come
and put him down.

336
00:19:04.639 --> 00:19:07.040
Great. So you're taking orders
from a madman.

337
00:19:07.042 --> 00:19:08.608
No. he wasn't mad then.

338
00:19:09.511 --> 00:19:12.378
Cain resisted the Mark
for a long time.

339
00:19:12.380 --> 00:19:15.014
then I came. kicking up trouble
about the Blade.

340
00:19:15.016 --> 00:19:16.698
I sent him down this path.
This is on me.

341
00:19:16.699 --> 00:19:18.566
It doesn't mean you have to be
the one to go after him.

342
00:19:18.568 --> 00:19:19.312
Yes. it does.

343
00:19:19.336 --> 00:19:21.690
And there's only one thing
that can kill him.

344
00:19:23.373 --> 00:19:25.873
The Blade.

345
00:19:25.875 --> 00:19:28.242
Dean's right.

346
00:19:30.146 --> 00:19:35.616
Dean. wielding the Blade
against Cain himself...

347
00:19:37.453 --> 00:19:39.554
...win or lose.

348
00:19:39.556 --> 00:19:42.323
you may never come back
from that fight.

349
00:19:48.064 --> 00:19:51.566
I know.

350
00:19:51.708 --> 00:19:54.909
I'll need a demon force
to get us past her security.

351
00:19:54.911 --> 00:19:56.944
2 units of 10
should suffice.

352
00:19:56.946 --> 00:19:58.312
Once we're inside.

353
00:19:58.314 --> 00:20:00.448
we'll want to throw her
off guard.

354
00:20:00.450 --> 00:20:02.516
mess with her head
a little bit.

355
00:20:02.518 --> 00:20:06.520
So I thought...
Rune of Amaranth.

356
00:20:06.522 --> 00:20:09.724
Illusion work. Smart.

357
00:20:10.993 --> 00:20:13.694
Excuse me.
I'll be right back.

358
00:20:13.796 --> 00:20:16.397
Well. well. well.
if it isn't --

359
00:20:16.399 --> 00:20:18.098
Cain's back.

360
00:20:18.100 --> 00:20:20.100
He's gone dark.
and I need the Blade.

361
00:20:20.102 --> 00:20:22.236
Why would I do that
for you?

362
00:20:22.238 --> 00:20:23.704
Because you have
as much reason

363
00:20:23.706 --> 00:20:25.472
to want Cain off the board
as anyone.

364
00:20:25.474 --> 00:20:29.410
Cain has a kill list.
and you're on it.

365
00:20:36.819 --> 00:20:39.353
What do you say. Crowley?
You in?

366
00:20:39.355 --> 00:20:41.889
Yes.

367
00:20:41.891 --> 00:20:45.059
Good. I'll text you
the location.

368
00:20:45.061 --> 00:20:46.894
Once she's well flustered.

369
00:20:46.896 --> 00:20:49.597
I've got
an especially nasty spell

370
00:20:49.599 --> 00:20:51.232
to finish her off with.

371
00:20:51.234 --> 00:20:52.700
Mother.
it's not happening.

372
00:20:52.702 --> 00:20:54.401
What?
Not today.

373
00:20:54.403 --> 00:20:56.403
Where are you going?
Something's come up.

374
00:20:56.405 --> 00:21:00.207
Olivette can wait.
This can't.

375
00:21:00.209 --> 00:21:02.943
Is that
what I think it is?!

376
00:21:02.945 --> 00:21:05.145
Not that it's
any of your business.

377
00:21:05.147 --> 00:21:06.580
Let me guess.

378
00:21:06.582 --> 00:21:09.550
Bringing it to your wee pal.
the Winchester boy.

379
00:21:09.552 --> 00:21:11.485
You'd give that
to the one person

380
00:21:11.487 --> 00:21:13.587
who can harness its power
against you.

381
00:21:13.589 --> 00:21:14.855
He's a threat to you!

382
00:21:14.857 --> 00:21:17.258
We've a common enemy.
a bigger threat.

383
00:21:17.260 --> 00:21:19.226
Well. if he's not a threat
to your life.

384
00:21:19.228 --> 00:21:21.362
he's certainly a threat
to your credibility.

385
00:21:21.364 --> 00:21:23.998
We've talked about what
this does to your reputation.

386
00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:26.433
We are not having
this conversation.

387
00:21:26.435 --> 00:21:28.769
Consorting with hunters!

388
00:21:28.771 --> 00:21:30.271
Oh. me. Oh. my.

389
00:21:30.273 --> 00:21:32.806
You honestly believe
that they're your friends.

390
00:21:32.808 --> 00:21:35.409
that they care about you?!

391
00:21:39.348 --> 00:21:41.148
Kid here?

392
00:21:41.150 --> 00:21:42.750
He's nearby.

393
00:21:42.752 --> 00:21:44.285
Upstairs in the barn.

394
00:21:44.287 --> 00:21:46.921
He's playing with
a basketball.

395
00:21:46.923 --> 00:21:49.590
Cain will strike soon.

396
00:21:49.592 --> 00:21:51.992
Maybe tonight. maybe tomorrow.
but soon.

397
00:21:51.994 --> 00:21:54.228
And when he does --
yeah. I got it.

398
00:21:54.230 --> 00:21:56.363
You charge in
with the Blade solo.

399
00:21:56.365 --> 00:21:58.232
And the kid?

400
00:21:58.234 --> 00:22:00.434
What. we just watch and wait
until Cain attacks?

401
00:22:00.436 --> 00:22:02.269
I thought this was
a rescue mission.

402
00:22:02.271 --> 00:22:04.371
We save the kid
after Cain shows.

403
00:22:04.373 --> 00:22:07.374
We know what Cain's after.
That's our only advantage.

404
00:22:07.376 --> 00:22:09.810
We want to trap Cain.
we use it.

405
00:22:09.812 --> 00:22:10.978
A 12-year-old as bait.

406
00:22:10.980 --> 00:22:12.780
I can't believe
what I'm hearing.

407
00:22:12.782 --> 00:22:14.348
Neither can I.

408
00:22:16.852 --> 00:22:18.452
What's the matter.
Crowley?

409
00:22:18.454 --> 00:22:20.254
You suddenly grow
a conscience?

410
00:22:20.256 --> 00:22:21.822
Too good to put a minor
in danger?

411
00:22:21.824 --> 00:22:24.058
Don't give a damn
about the kid.

412
00:22:24.060 --> 00:22:26.393
I'm talking about
the risk to us.

413
00:22:26.395 --> 00:22:28.595
There is no us.

414
00:22:28.597 --> 00:22:31.632
You're here for one reason.
That's to hand me the Blade.

415
00:22:31.634 --> 00:22:33.133
Yeah. about that.

416
00:22:33.135 --> 00:22:35.803
Seeing as this is shaping up
to be one of those.

417
00:22:35.805 --> 00:22:39.373
uh. two-step capture then kill
kind of deals.

418
00:22:39.375 --> 00:22:42.076
I think
your buddies would agree

419
00:22:42.078 --> 00:22:44.278
it's better to keep the Blade
out of your hands

420
00:22:44.280 --> 00:22:45.746
until we've got Cain
sewn up.

421
00:22:45.748 --> 00:22:47.748
just to be safe.

422
00:22:53.622 --> 00:22:56.457
Now. back to this plan
of yours.

423
00:23:13.609 --> 00:23:16.343
So...

424
00:23:16.345 --> 00:23:21.048
If this works
and we capture Cain.

425
00:23:21.050 --> 00:23:22.649
then what?

426
00:23:22.651 --> 00:23:25.719
We'll cross that bridge
when we c--

427
00:23:25.721 --> 00:23:27.688
<i>if</i> we come to it.

428
00:23:31.227 --> 00:23:32.893
You know last week.

429
00:23:32.895 --> 00:23:35.696
when I said that I would go down
swinging when the time came?

430
00:23:37.066 --> 00:23:40.034
I meant that
I was at peace with that.

431
00:23:40.036 --> 00:23:44.772
I just didn't realize
the time would come so soon.

432
00:23:44.774 --> 00:23:47.908
you know. like right now.

433
00:23:56.819 --> 00:23:59.153
I'm scared. Sam.

434
00:24:05.661 --> 00:24:07.361
♪ ...down in Mexico ♪

435
00:24:07.363 --> 00:24:10.097
♪ got hitched
in the house of gin ♪

436
00:24:10.099 --> 00:24:13.167
♪ my hangover will never end ♪

437
00:24:16.839 --> 00:24:18.639
Someone there?

438
00:24:24.547 --> 00:24:27.347
Hello. Austin.

439
00:24:27.349 --> 00:24:30.017
What are you doing here?

440
00:24:30.019 --> 00:24:33.153
I'm here to kill you.

441
00:24:33.155 --> 00:24:35.756
No. you won't.

442
00:24:35.758 --> 00:24:37.558
Run!

443
00:24:39.462 --> 00:24:41.261
You can't stop me.

444
00:25:21.904 --> 00:25:23.203
Don't.

445
00:25:23.205 --> 00:25:25.205
Please don't.

446
00:25:34.550 --> 00:25:36.250
Illusion spell.

447
00:25:36.252 --> 00:25:39.253
Oh. yeah.
The real Austin is long gone.

448
00:25:39.255 --> 00:25:42.523
18th-century magic.

449
00:25:42.525 --> 00:25:46.693
If I had to hazard a guess.
Rune of Amaranth.

450
00:25:46.695 --> 00:25:47.995
Good eye.

451
00:25:47.997 --> 00:25:51.131
Something I picked up
from my mother.

452
00:25:53.068 --> 00:25:55.936
Well. I know you fear me.

453
00:25:55.938 --> 00:25:58.539
I can only assume...

454
00:26:01.443 --> 00:26:04.278
Oh. Clever.

455
00:26:05.814 --> 00:26:07.614
Won't hold me for long.
you know.

456
00:26:07.616 --> 00:26:10.284
It won't need to.

457
00:26:24.033 --> 00:26:27.167
Cass. hey. you okay?

458
00:26:27.169 --> 00:26:29.403
I'm fine.

459
00:26:29.405 --> 00:26:31.004
It worked?

460
00:26:31.006 --> 00:26:32.706
Yeah.

461
00:26:32.708 --> 00:26:34.708
My turn.

462
00:26:34.710 --> 00:26:36.043
Dean. look.
we want to help.

463
00:26:36.045 --> 00:26:37.644
No.

464
00:26:37.646 --> 00:26:41.381
No. with you in the ring.
it'd just be a liability.

465
00:26:41.383 --> 00:26:41.985
Dean?

466
00:26:42.008 --> 00:26:44.009
I'd be too worried about
what he could do to you...

467
00:26:44.820 --> 00:26:47.221
Or what I could.

468
00:26:49.225 --> 00:26:51.191
Plus.
I need you three out here

469
00:26:51.193 --> 00:26:54.094
to take out
whatever comes out of there.

470
00:26:55.898 --> 00:26:59.600
And I'm serious.
I mean whatever comes out.

471
00:27:01.170 --> 00:27:03.203
Happily.

472
00:27:15.451 --> 00:27:17.317
What guarantee do I have

473
00:27:17.319 --> 00:27:20.621
that you'll give it back
when you're done?

474
00:27:20.623 --> 00:27:22.823
If I survive
and I come out of there

475
00:27:22.825 --> 00:27:24.758
and I<i> don't</i> give it back.

476
00:27:24.760 --> 00:27:28.128
you'll all have a much bigger
problem on your hands.

477
00:27:38.841 --> 00:27:40.841
Dean?

478
00:27:47.483 --> 00:27:49.516
I'm good.

479
00:28:36.375 --> 00:28:38.609
Hello. Dean.

480
00:28:42.248 --> 00:28:45.282
At a loss for words.
my son?

481
00:28:45.284 --> 00:28:48.719
Allow me.

482
00:28:48.721 --> 00:28:53.290
This is the part where
you tell me it's not too late

483
00:28:53.292 --> 00:28:56.494
and I can lay down arms.

484
00:28:56.496 --> 00:28:58.863
abandon my mission.

485
00:28:58.865 --> 00:29:00.898
“We don't have to fight”.

486
00:29:00.900 --> 00:29:06.370
I'll spare us
the formalities.

487
00:29:06.372 --> 00:29:08.973
You're past talking down.

488
00:29:08.975 --> 00:29:10.608
Cain.
you're fully mental.

489
00:29:10.610 --> 00:29:13.144
Oh. I prefer to think
I've finally gotten clear.

490
00:29:13.146 --> 00:29:16.147
When I made my bargain
with Lucifer.

491
00:29:16.149 --> 00:29:17.381
killed Abel.

492
00:29:17.383 --> 00:29:21.085
I released a stain
upon the earth.

493
00:29:21.087 --> 00:29:24.955
a stain deeper
and far more lasting

494
00:29:24.957 --> 00:29:27.091
than mere precedence.

495
00:29:27.093 --> 00:29:30.694
Your bloodline's tainted.
so you say.

496
00:29:30.696 --> 00:29:32.563
So I know.

497
00:29:33.966 --> 00:29:35.699
Not all killers
are my descendants.

498
00:29:35.701 --> 00:29:37.601
and not all my descendants
are killers.

499
00:29:37.603 --> 00:29:39.003
but enough are.

500
00:29:39.005 --> 00:29:40.671
enough for me to know

501
00:29:40.673 --> 00:29:43.140
that extinguishing them
is the least I owe this world.

502
00:29:43.142 --> 00:29:47.278
Can you honestly tell me
that humanity's not better off

503
00:29:47.280 --> 00:29:50.815
with fewer Tommys
and fewer Leons...

504
00:29:50.817 --> 00:29:52.483
Fewer yous?

505
00:29:54.854 --> 00:29:56.520
And what about the kid?

506
00:29:56.522 --> 00:29:59.857
He could go either way.

507
00:29:59.859 --> 00:30:01.725
I prefer to be thorough.

508
00:30:03.863 --> 00:30:09.233
How's it feel. Dean.
holding the Blade again?

509
00:30:13.105 --> 00:30:15.639
It feels like
a means to an end.

510
00:30:30.189 --> 00:30:32.556
Then do it.

511
00:31:34.453 --> 00:31:35.853
That seems a bit weaker

512
00:31:35.855 --> 00:31:38.722
than I would expect from you
with the Blade.

513
00:31:40.793 --> 00:31:42.826
I think you can do better.

514
00:31:46.632 --> 00:31:48.599
Unless...

515
00:31:53.839 --> 00:31:56.206
You're holding back.

516
00:31:59.011 --> 00:32:01.512
What is it. Dean?

517
00:32:01.514 --> 00:32:03.948
Do you think if you hold back
just enough. you won't succumb.

518
00:32:03.950 --> 00:32:07.117
that you'll leave this fight
the same as you entered?!

519
00:32:08.487 --> 00:32:11.555
Look to my example. boy!

520
00:32:11.557 --> 00:32:15.259
There is no resisting the Mark
or the Blade.

521
00:32:15.261 --> 00:32:17.528
There is only remission
and relapse!

522
00:32:26.572 --> 00:32:31.275
You told me
that this day would come.

523
00:32:33.079 --> 00:32:36.146
You told me
that I would have to kill you.

524
00:32:36.148 --> 00:32:39.850
Is that so?

525
00:32:44.457 --> 00:32:47.858
I'm afraid you've misunderstood
my intentions here. Dean.

526
00:32:47.860 --> 00:32:51.729
When your pet angel
found my burial site.

527
00:32:51.731 --> 00:32:56.433
I thought about ending him
and swatting him like a fly.

528
00:32:56.435 --> 00:32:59.870
But then
I thought about you.

529
00:32:59.872 --> 00:33:01.171
Your biggest weakness.

530
00:33:01.173 --> 00:33:03.807
the thing I noticed
the moment I met you.

531
00:33:03.809 --> 00:33:07.845
your courage.
your reckless bravado.

532
00:33:07.847 --> 00:33:10.547
I let him go.

533
00:33:10.549 --> 00:33:12.816
knowing that he would
report back to you.

534
00:33:12.818 --> 00:33:15.285
knowing you would bring
into battle

535
00:33:15.287 --> 00:33:17.554
the one thing
that can kill me.

536
00:33:17.556 --> 00:33:21.325
the one thing
I truly want.

537
00:33:33.439 --> 00:33:36.607
Oh. it's been too long.

538
00:33:38.010 --> 00:33:41.211
That old feeling
makes me wonder

539
00:33:41.213 --> 00:33:43.514
how I ever had the strength
to resist.

540
00:33:46.652 --> 00:33:48.085
This may be hard
to believe

541
00:33:48.087 --> 00:33:50.054
in light of what
I'm about to do to you.

542
00:33:50.056 --> 00:33:51.955
but I care about you.
Dean.

543
00:33:51.957 --> 00:33:53.323
I truly do.

544
00:33:53.325 --> 00:33:56.693
But I know
I'm doing you a favor.

545
00:33:56.695 --> 00:33:58.295
I'm saving you.

546
00:33:58.297 --> 00:34:01.198
Saving me from what?

547
00:34:01.200 --> 00:34:03.133
From your fate.

548
00:34:05.504 --> 00:34:07.337
Has it never occurred
to you?

549
00:34:07.339 --> 00:34:09.506
Have you never
mused upon the fact

550
00:34:09.508 --> 00:34:11.508
that you're living my life
in reverse?

551
00:34:11.510 --> 00:34:15.045
My story began
when I killed my brother.

552
00:34:15.047 --> 00:34:18.048
and that's where your story
inevitably will end.

553
00:34:18.050 --> 00:34:21.251
No. Never.

554
00:34:22.121 --> 00:34:24.588
It's called the Mark of Cain
for a reason!

555
00:34:24.590 --> 00:34:28.025
First --
first. you'd kill Crowley.

556
00:34:28.027 --> 00:34:29.493
There'd be some strange.
mixed feelings on that one.

557
00:34:29.495 --> 00:34:30.694
but you'd have your reason.

558
00:34:30.696 --> 00:34:33.530
You'd get it done.
no remorse.

559
00:34:33.532 --> 00:34:35.666
And then you'd kill the angel.
Castiel.

560
00:34:35.668 --> 00:34:37.101
Now. that one --

561
00:34:37.103 --> 00:34:41.572
that I suspect
would hurt something awful.

562
00:34:41.574 --> 00:34:43.140
And then!

563
00:34:43.142 --> 00:34:45.409
Then would come the murder
you'd never survive.

564
00:34:45.411 --> 00:34:48.112
the one that would
finally turn you

565
00:34:48.114 --> 00:34:50.514
into as much of a savage
as it did me.

566
00:34:50.516 --> 00:34:51.815
No.

567
00:34:51.817 --> 00:34:53.317
Your brother. Sam.

568
00:34:53.319 --> 00:34:57.721
The only thing standing
between you and that destiny

569
00:34:57.723 --> 00:34:59.189
is this Blade.

570
00:35:00.960 --> 00:35:03.427
You're welcome. my son.

571
00:35:25.117 --> 00:35:28.152
What's the matter?

572
00:35:33.859 --> 00:35:37.027
Tell me
I don't have to do this.

573
00:35:39.598 --> 00:35:41.532
Tell me that you'll stop.

574
00:35:42.868 --> 00:35:45.669
Tell me that you<i> can</i> stop!

575
00:35:47.373 --> 00:35:49.740
I will never stop.

576
00:36:54.807 --> 00:36:56.506
Dean?

577
00:36:58.277 --> 00:37:03.614
Dean. the Blade.

578
00:37:30.943 --> 00:37:33.644
You lied to me.

579
00:37:35.047 --> 00:37:37.481
It's not the first time
today.

580
00:37:39.985 --> 00:37:44.788
Cain's list --
you weren't on it.

581
00:37:52.298 --> 00:37:54.929
Hey. hey. hey.

582
00:37:54.930 --> 00:37:57.638
You did it.

583
00:37:58.621 --> 00:38:00.387
Dean. you did it.

584
00:38:24.831 --> 00:38:26.831
Fergus...

585
00:38:26.833 --> 00:38:31.769
I don't want to hear it.
the “I told you sos.” not now.

586
00:38:35.675 --> 00:38:37.608
What are you doing?

587
00:38:37.610 --> 00:38:41.145
What's it look like?
I'm leaving.

588
00:38:41.147 --> 00:38:43.781
Another
petty manipulation.

589
00:38:45.552 --> 00:38:47.251
No.

590
00:38:47.253 --> 00:38:50.955
Then what. mother?
What do you want from me?!

591
00:38:52.759 --> 00:38:56.727
You can't understand
my disappointment...

592
00:38:56.729 --> 00:38:58.496
or my pride.

593
00:38:58.498 --> 00:39:01.032
You don't know this.

594
00:39:01.034 --> 00:39:04.502
but after I left you.
after I was forced to leave you.

595
00:39:04.504 --> 00:39:07.638
I heard of your death --
your mortal death.

596
00:39:08.975 --> 00:39:10.875
I thought you were
gone to me forever.

597
00:39:10.877 --> 00:39:15.079
Then.
hundreds of years later

598
00:39:15.081 --> 00:39:17.848
and thousands
of miles away.

599
00:39:17.850 --> 00:39:22.820
I find you.
the King of Hell.

600
00:39:22.822 --> 00:39:26.791
and not by luck
or accident.

601
00:39:26.793 --> 00:39:31.796
You made that happen
all by yourself.

602
00:39:33.533 --> 00:39:34.932
You're not a mother.

603
00:39:34.934 --> 00:39:37.468
You can't know what
that pride felt like.

604
00:39:37.470 --> 00:39:39.270
how huge it was.

605
00:39:39.272 --> 00:39:44.709
But can you try to imagine.
for me?

606
00:39:44.711 --> 00:39:50.014
Now do you understand
why it breaks my heart

607
00:39:50.016 --> 00:39:54.952
to see what a colossal numb nut
you've become?!

608
00:39:54.954 --> 00:39:56.454
You've got the crown.

609
00:39:56.456 --> 00:39:58.556
but you're no ruler.
not really!

610
00:39:58.558 --> 00:40:02.093
A sad. bored. wee boy
on the throne

611
00:40:02.095 --> 00:40:05.096
who'll flop ass-up
the second those Winchesters --

612
00:40:05.098 --> 00:40:08.499
hunters who'd as soon see you
dead as have you to tea --

613
00:40:08.501 --> 00:40:09.934
ask you to.

614
00:40:11.537 --> 00:40:13.638
You're no king.
not anymore.

615
00:40:20.113 --> 00:40:22.947
You're their bitch.

616
00:40:41.701 --> 00:40:46.904
Dean. um. you know.
what you did back there.

617
00:40:46.906 --> 00:40:49.206
it was incredible.

618
00:40:49.208 --> 00:40:55.713
You know. if you can do that
without losing yourself.

619
00:40:55.715 --> 00:40:59.350
that's cause for hope.
even without a cure.

620
00:40:59.352 --> 00:41:03.020
Yeah.

621
00:41:03.022 --> 00:41:04.989
Maybe.

622
00:41:09.262 --> 00:41:12.430
So. where's the Blade?

623
00:41:12.432 --> 00:41:15.433
Somewhere safe.

624
00:41:15.435 --> 00:41:18.002
Good.

625
00:41:19.806 --> 00:41:21.639
Well. if you guys
will excuse me.

626
00:41:21.641 --> 00:41:24.408
I think I am gonna go sleep
for about four days.

627
00:41:24.410 --> 00:41:26.677
Of course.

628
00:41:39.559 --> 00:41:41.926
How is he?

629
00:41:44.924 --> 00:41:45.924
Sam?

630
00:41:45.951 --> 00:41:48.384
Cass...

631
00:41:49.268 --> 00:41:51.502
Dean's in trouble.

632
00:41:54.834 --> 00:42:01.334
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>
